HEADWORD: Apheresis
<hw>A*pher"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aphaeresis</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to take away; <?/ + <?/ to
take.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The dropping of a
letter or syllable from the beginning of a word; <it>e. g</it>., cute
for <xex>a</xex>cute.</def>⟦br⟧
